HEADWORD: Pyocyanin
<hw>Py`o*cy"a*nin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ pus +
<?/ dark blue.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A blue coloring
matter found in the pus from old sores, supposed to be formed through
the agency of a species of bacterium (<spn>Bacillus
pyocyaneus</spn>).</def><-- now, Pseudomonas aeruginosa
<chform>C13H10N2O</chform>-->⟦br⟧
